definitions.definition: A reading or an act of reading, especially of an actor's part of a play or a piece of stored data.
examples: I had a read of the evening papers.

definitions.definition: Something to be read; a written work.
examples: His thrillers are always a gripping read .

definitions.definition: A person's interpretation or impression of something.
examples: What's your read of the current political situation?
On the quarterback's first read of the situation, his target receiver was not open.

definitions.definition: An instance of reading ( “ calling attention to someone's flaws; a taunt or insult ” ) .
labels: at first especially in the black LGBTQ community
definitions.label_groups: at first especially in the black LGBTQ community

definitions.definition: The identification of a specific sequence of genes in a genome or bases in a nucleic acid string.
